8800 Morbid curiosity was the only driving force that fabricated my will to hover my mouse over the entry and click it. Little did I know i would discover a side of me I never knew. They always say that knowing oneself is a key aspect in life that can positively affect many actions you wish to undertake. I agree with statement, though this doujin led me to uncover a veil and discover a kind of darkness, a revolting side of me, that I would've been able to say with utmost certainty, that I never wanted to know. Thus, it pains me to say that after having experienced mochi's work of asuka kudou, my viewpoint shifted...in what direction, I wonder...The mind sure is a strange thing. To this day, I still do not know what it is about a 146cm girl getting brutally ravaged whilst being asphyxiated after having her limbs lobbed off and eyes gouged out that is able to take me to heights words can't begin to describe. I’ll see myself out….
